39 (D) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall designate a member of the
40 committee as chairperson of the committee.
41 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
42 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
43 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
44 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
45 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
46 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
47 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
48 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
49 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
50 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
51 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
52 or state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the committee,
53 but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the performance of their
54 duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they are reimbursed for
55 expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
56 (C) Members of the committee who are not legislators, state officials, or state
57 employees shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount the same as that
58 specified in subsection (b) of Code Section 45-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia
59 Annotated, as well as the mileage or transportation allowance authorized for state
60 employees.
61 (D) The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member
62 of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
63 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
64 appropriated to the House of Representatives; except that funds for the reimbursement
65 of the expenses of state officials, other than legislative members, and for the
